        "The range of materials that survive glacial entombment is astonishing. Leather, wool, hair, wood, and even foodstuffs have been recovered in states of preservation that conventional burial in soil almost never achieves. The chemistry of ice entombment is straightforward: in sub-zero anaerobic conditions, the bacteria and fungi that ordinarily drive decomposition cannot function.",
